(45, 'ACCT', 'ACCT-5901', '5', '1', 'Graduate Business Practicum in Accounting', 'Prerequisite: Student must be in the accounting emphasis. This course provides one to three hours of credit in association with completion of an acceptable accounting industry internship/practicum. Students selecting this option will be responsible for locating an appropriate industry opportunity. This is an optional course and does not substitute for any leveling, core, or elective courses. The curriculum practical training course period extends through an entire semester.'),
