(377, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-1103', '1', '3', 'Introduction to Exercise Science', 'An overview of the field of exercise science. Exercise physiology, testing, prescription, sports nutrition, and biomechanics are all introduced in this course. A large focus of the course is the overall evidence regarding the long-term health benefits of physical activity. Finally, careers in exercise science are discussed. Same as NESP-1013. This course is normally offered in the spring semester.'),
