(385, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-1314', '1', '4', 'General Zoology', 'A study of the dynamics of animals with emphasis on structure, function, heredity, ecology and behavior with a survey of various invertebrate and vertebrate phyla. Lecture ? 3 hours; Laboratory ? 3 hours. This course is normally offered in the spring semester.'),
