(387, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-2013', '2', '3', 'Biology I Foundations of Life', 'A study of the basic unit of life: a cell, including cell structure, energy transfer, metabolic processes, reproduction, and genetics. Lecture ? 2 hours per week; Lab/discussion sessions ? 2 hours per week. Not applicable for credit in a science major other than Science Education. This course is normally offered every semester.'),
