(392, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-2033', '2', '3', 'Nutrition', 'A study of basic principles of human nutrition applied to health and diseases of the individual, family, and community. Course topics include biochemical aspects of nutrients, nutrient needs throughout the life cycle, and medical nutrition therapy, and its role in different medical conditions. This course is normally offered every semester.'),
