(400, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-2314', '2', '4', 'Genetics', 'A study of the principles of heredity and variation with emphasis on Mendelian genetics, genetic aberrations, molecular genetics, and current genetics research. Lab experiences reinforce concepts of heredity through a genome annotation research project, DNA isolation, manipulation, and analysis. Lecture - 3 hours; Laboratory - 3 hours. This course is normally offered in the spring semester.'),
