(408, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-2913', '2', '3', 'Bio Statistics', 'Prerequisites: MATH-1223. A 14-week, introductory course in applied statistics for the biological sciences. The course will focus on generation of hypotheses, experimental design, and analysis of experimental data. Students will determine proper sample size, categorization of experimental groups, and statistical tests to test hypotheses. Additionally, students will become proficient in the use of commonly used statistics software. This course is normally offered in the fall semester.'),
