(410, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-3023', '3', '3', 'Biomechanics', 'Prerequisite: PHYS 1114. Attention is given to the mechanical and anatomical aspects of human movement across modalities of exercise and physical activity. The class applies kinematic and kinetic principles to the analysis of human movement. A particular focus of this class would be injury prevention through utilization of proper biomechanics. Same as NESP-3023. This course is normally offered in the fall semester.'),
