(433, 'BIOL', 'BIOL-3514', '3', '4', 'Ornithology', 'The natural history of birds with emphasis on U.S. species including avian ecology, anatomy and physiology. Lab experiences are built around field trips devoted to species identification and behavior. Lecture ? 3 hours; Laboratory ? 3 hours. This course is normally offered in the spring semester of odd numbered years.'),
