(1268, 'ENGL', 'ENGL-1113', '1', '3', 'English Comp I', 'The first course in college-level writing using contemporary technology. The course emphasizes the composing process, analytical thinking, various types of writing, basic research methods and documentation. Writing includes a journal, a personal essay, a research report, analytical essays and a short research paper sustaining a thesis. Students enrolled in ENGL-1113-English Composition I must make a grade of C\" or better in order to enroll in ENGL-1213-English Composition II. This course is normally offered every semester.\"'),
(1269, 'ENGL', 'ENGL-1213', '1', '3', 'English Comp II', 'Prerequisites: ENGL-1113 with a grade of C\" or better. The second and final course in the composition series'),
