(1319, 'ENGL', 'ENGL-4733', '4', '3', 'Senior Capstone', 'Prerequisites: Senior standing and departmental approval. A capstone course giving Language and Literature majors the opportunity to synthesize previous work, to interact with the faculty at an advanced level, and to practice research skills in preparation for graduate school or for entry into their profession. This course is normally offered every fall semester.'),
