(1398, 'ENGR', 'ENGR-4701', '4', '1', 'Senior Engineering Seminar', 'Prerequisite: CENG-4732, ELEC-4732 or MECH-4732. Preparation for a transition from college to career. Topics include professionalism and ethics, resume and interview preparation, job and graduate school search, and leadership in and contribution to a local congregation. Presentations from potential employers and engineering alumni. Lecture - 1 hours. This course is normally offered in the fall semester.'),
