(1903, 'HRMT', 'HRMT-5901', '5', '1', 'Grad Business Pract in Human Resources', 'Prerequisite: Student must be in the Human Resources Management emphasis. Consent of Graduate School of Business Chair and instructor required. This course provides one to three hours of credit in association with completion of an acceptable Human Resources Management related internship/practicum. Students selecting this option will be responsible for locating an appropriate industry opportunity. This is an elective course and may be substituted for one of the MBA Human Resources Management emphasis elective courses. The curriculum practical training course period extends through an entire semester. Practicum usage is limited to a maximum of 3 hours and may be used within the degrees requirement.'),
(1904, 'HSMT', 'HSMT-5243', '5', '3', 'Foundations of Integrated Health Care Management', 'The course examines the organization and operations of health care systems in general. It covers the topics of board, management and medical staff roles and responsibilities; health care policy; financial management; contracting and negotiations; and insurance.'),
(1905, 'HSMT', 'HSMT-5253', '5', '3', 'Hospital Operations Management', 'This course covers operational issues of health care administration. It focuses on hospital operations, but other types of organizations are discussed. Primary emphasis is on planning, forecasting, scheduling, staffing, inventory, logistics, and quality control issues in hospitals. The course also covers public health and medical specialties requirements.'),
(1906, 'HSMT', 'HSMT-5263', '5', '3', 'Practice Management in Health Care Systems', 'This course emphasizes planning, implementation, and control in managing health care professional practices. It examines directing and training professional staff, legal, and organizational structures used in practice management groups, and the importance of patient satisfaction in health care practices. Financial issues related to practice management are also covered.'),
