(2085, 'MATH', 'MATH-5513', '5', '3', 'Linear Algebra', 'Prerequisite: Acceptance into the M.S.E. program. This is a graduate mathematics class designed for engineering students. Topics include matrices, systems of equations, vector spaces, linear transformations, orthogonality, and eigenvalues. Special attention will be given to engineering applications of these topics.'),
