(2323, 'MKTG', 'MKTG-5901', '5', '1', 'Graduate Business Practicum in Marketing', 'Prerequisite: Student must be in the marketing emphasis. Consent of Graduate School of Business Chair and instructor required. This course provides one to three hours of credit in association with completion of an acceptable marketing related internship/practicum. Students selecting this option will be responsible for locating an appropriate industry opportunity. This is an elective course and may be substituted for one of the MBA Marketing emphasis elective courses. The curriculum practical training course period extends through an entire semester. Practicum usage is limited to a maximum of 3 hours and may be used within the degrees requirement.'),
