(2397, 'MUSC', 'MUSC-1581', '1', '1', 'Class Piano I', 'An introduction to piano playing for the student with little or no prior keyboard experience. Instruction will stress understanding notation of pitch and rhythm; playing with appropriate fingering, articulation and dynamics; gaining technical facility and coordination between hands; playing pieces in major and minor five-finger patterns; and playing melodies with triad accompaniments. Some selections will be memorized. Class - 2 hours. This course is normally offered every semester.'),
