(2914, 'SOCI', 'SOCI-4633', '4', '3', 'Intercultural Communication I', 'Prerequisite: ENGL-1213. A survey of the basic concepts of how people communicate effectively across cultural boundaries, with special attention given to the complex nature culture plays in communication. SOCI-4633 fosters in students an understanding and appreciation of their own culture and cultural patterns of communication and those of other cultures. Same as COMM-4633, ENGL-4633 and MISS-4633. This course is normally offered in the spring semester of odd numbered years.'),
(2915, 'SOCI', 'SOCI-4643', '4', '3', 'Intercultural Communication II', 'Prerequisite: ENGL-1213. A continuation of SOCI-4633, typically taught while a student is living in a foreign culture. Same as ENGL-4643 and MISS-4643. This course is normally offered in the fall semester of odd numbered years.'),
